-- Brazilian Stock Movers: CPFL Energia, Eletropaulo, Oi and Rossi
-- B y   D e n y s e   G o d o y
-- 2012-07-03T16:02:28Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-03/brazilian-stock-movers-cpfl-energia-eletropaulo-oi-and-rossi.html
The following companies are having
 unusual  price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of 12:29 p.m. local time.
Preferred shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index rose 2.2 percent to 55,924.84  Eletropaulo Metropolitana SA (ELPL4 BS), a unit of  AES
Corp. (AES)  that is Brazil’s biggest power utility by market value,
fell 11 percent to 22.64 reais, poised for the lowest close
since October 2008. The country’s regulator cut the rates
Eletropaulo charges consumers by 9.3 percent, effective
tomorrow.  CPFL Energia SA (CPFE3)  (CPFE3 BS), Brazil’s second-biggest power
utility by market capitalization, fell 4.2 percent to 24.58
reais, the steepest intraday drop since May 21. The stock was
cut to equivalent of sell from neutral at  Barclays Capital  on
valuation.  Oi SA (OIBR4)  (OIBR4 BS), a fixed and mobile telecommunications
operator, advanced 4.7 percent to 8.90 reais.  Banco Bradesco
SA (BBDC4) ’s brokerage raised its recommendation to the equivalent of
buy from neutral, citing expectations for improved revenue and a
new dividend distribution plan.  Rossi Residencial SA (RSID3)  (RSID3 BS) rallied 6.5 percent to 4.97
reais. A close at that level would be the highest since June 22.
The homebuilder dismissed about 100 employees, newspaper Valor
Economico reported, citing an unidentified source. Rossi’s press
office didn’t immediate comment when contacted by Bloomberg
News.  To contact the reporter on this story:
